We use synthetic division.
\[
\begin{array}{rrrrrrr}
\multicolumn{1}{r|}{-5} & {1} & 0 & -23 & 11 & -14 & 10 \\
\multicolumn{1}{r|}{} & & -5& 25& -10 & -5 & 95 \\
\cline{2-7}
 & 1& -5& 2& 1 & -19& \multicolumn{1}{|r}{105} \\
\end{array}
\]So we have a quotient of $\boxed{x^4-5x^3+2x^2+x-19}$ and a remainder of $105$.
